        44.29 LAB: Swapping variables Define a method named swapValues that takes an array of four integers as a parameter, swaps array elements at indices 0 and 1, and swaps array elements at indices 2 and 3. Then write a main program that reads four integers from input and stores the integers in an array in positions 0 to 3. The main program should call function swapValues() to swap array's values and print the swapped values on a single line separated with spaces.
